"1164":"1164","1075":"1075","4 April 1068":"4 April 1068","1040":"1040","1073":"1073","1050":"1050","1072":"1072","1092":"1092","1070":"1070","Lucé, Orne, Basse-Normandie, France":"Lucé, Orne, Lower Normandy, France","Little Missenden, Buckinghamshire, England":"Little Missenden, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom","Normandy, France":"Normandy, France","Erith, Kent, England":"Erith, Kent, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Maunsel","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: variant of   Mansell  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Mansell","meanings":["English (mainly West Midlands):","(of Norman origin): habitational name from Old French <i>mansel</i> ‘inhabitant of Le Mans or the surrounding area of Maine’. The place was originally named in Latin <i>(ad) Ceromannos</i>, from the name of the Gaulish tribe living there, the <i>Ceromanni</i>. The name was shortened to <i>Celmans</i> and then became <i>Le Mans</i> as a result of the mistaken identification of the first syllable with the Old French demonstrative adjective.","status name for a particular type of feudal tenant, Anglo-Norman French <i>mansel</i>, one who occupied a <i>manse</i> (from Late Latin <i>mansa</i> ‘dwelling’), a measure of land sufficient to support one family."]}]},{"name":"Henry","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["A perennially popular given name, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Henry Maunsel was born on 4 April 1068, in Normandy, France, his father, Philippe Maunsell, was 28 and his mother, Agnes Demoiselle de Montsorrel, was 19. He married Emma deLucy in 1089, in Lucé, Orne, Lower Normandy, France. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1100, in Erith, Kent, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 32."},"et":{"4 April 1068–1100":"4. aprill 1068–1100","1068–1100":"1068–1100","1070–Male":"1070–Surnud","1072–Male":"1072–Surnud","1073–Male":"1073–Surnud","1075–Male":"1075–Surnud","1068–Female":"1068–Surnud","1092–1164":"1092–1164","1040–Male":"1040–Surnud","1050–Female":"1050–Surnud","1068":"1068","1089":"1089","1100":"1100","1164":"1164","1075":"1075","4 April 1068":"4. aprill 1068","1040":"1040","1073":"1073","1050":"1050","1072":"1072","1092":"1092","1070":"1070","Lucé, Orne, Basse-Normandie, France":"Lucé, Orne, Basse-Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Little Missenden, Buckinghamshire, England":"Little Missenden, Buckinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Erith, Kent, England":"Erith, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"4 April 1068–1100":"4. huhtikuuta 1068–1100","1068–1100":"1068–1100","1070–Male":"1070–Kuollut","1072–Male":"1072–Kuollut","1073–Male":"1073–Kuollut","1075–Male":"1075–Kuollut","1068–Female":"1068–Kuollut","1092–1164":"1092–1164","1040–Male":"1040–Kuollut","1050–Female":"1050–Kuollut","1068":"1068","1089":"1089","1100":"1100","1164":"1164","1075":"1075","4 April 1068":"4. huhtikuuta 1068","1040":"1040","1073":"1073","1050":"1050","1072":"1072","1092":"1092","1070":"1070","Lucé, Orne, Basse-Normandie, France":"Lucé, Orne, Basse-Normandie, Ranska","Little Missenden, Buckinghamshire, England":"Little Missenden, Buckinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Ranska","Erith, Kent, England":"Erith, Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"4 April 1068–1100":"4 avril 1068–1100","1068–1100":"1068–1100","1070–Male":"1070–Décédé","1072–Male":"1072–Décédé","1073–Male"